Diageo Plc, Eurasia, National Express Group: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-04-21T00:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/diageo-plc-national-express-group-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index (UKX)  rose 125.39 points, or 2.13
percent, to 6,022.26. The  FTSE All-Share Index (ASX)  gained 2 percent
while Ireland’s ISEQ Index advanced 0.5 percent.  Diageo Plc (DGE)  : The world’s biggest distiller is
teaming up with U.S. buyout firm Bain Capital LLC for a possible
joint bid for Stock Spirits Group, the distilling and
distribution company owned by Oaktree Capital Management LLC,
said three people with knowledge of the matter. The stock rose
0.6 percent to 1,207 pence.  Eurasia Drilling Co. (EDCL LI): The Russian provider of
oilfield services listed in  London  may report full-year net
income of $232 million, according to the average of three
estimates compiled by Bloomberg. The stock rose 2.9 percent to
$32.30  National Express Group Plc (NEX)  : The U.K. bus and train
company facing demands for a breakup from No. 1 investor Elliott
Advisors Ltd., said the hedge fund increased its stake to 18.03
percent. The stock dropped 1.4 percent to 258.4 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Simpson in Toronto at 
